{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-37214].
  {panel}

Hi, I am not able to login to confluence page..and when i am trying to recover the password, it is asking to contact the system administrtor.
Can you please help to recover my password

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-37206].
  {panel}

Add option to allow restricted Confluence pages to show in HipChat.

When CONF-30853 and CONF-31768 were fixed it broke things for folks who want restricted content to go to a private HipChat room.

I would suggest on the integrations dialogue you include a fourth checkbox for each integration to allow restricted content.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-37197].
  {panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-37192].
  {panel}

*Background of the Request*

A customer has requested the ability to rate attachments. With a specific attachment rating we want the ability to rate attachments of a page, as shown in the attached image below.  Currently, this feature is not available in Attachment macro. 


As of now, there are no plugins available with such feature that can be used as a workaround.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-37189].
  {panel}

Right from https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Integrating+JIRA+with+FishEye I got 2 mails these days, [~jpaz] has edited and added information on.

As you can see in the attached mail source below, the links in the latest added section to page „Release Hub“ is broken.
{code}
<a class=
=3D"confluence-link unresolved" href=3D"#" style=3D"color: #3b73af; text-de=
coration: none"><span class=3D"diff-html-added" style=3D"font-size: 100%; b=
ackground-color: #ddfade;">Release Hub</span></a>
{code}

as you can see in the page storage https://confluence.atlassian.com/plugins/viewstorage/viewpagestorage.action?pageId=185729669 it was saved as
{code}
<ac:link><ri:page ri:content-title="Checking the progress of a version" /><ac:plain-text-link-body><![CDATA[Release Hub]]></ac:plain-text-link-body></ac:link>{code}

While classic saved anchor tags are accessible correctly, other ac:link already on the page broken too.
While neither the target page https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Checking+the+progress+of+a+version is restricted in any way, nor it was a problem in the past, I assume this is a *regression bug*.

----

