As [this JIRA request|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRA-25208], this one is to display the user and group names according to the directory that they belong.

  For example, if I have users/groups from a JIRA directory, LDAP and internal, I would have an option under the *User Management* that would display the directories that I have. Once clicking on the option, the users/groups displayed would be filtered to be displayed only from the selected directory. 

Another option would be to re-order the users/groups according to the directory that they are retrieved.
Filter by Directory in User/Group Browser

Current *workaround* is to perform SQL queries to achieve such feature:
*Alternative 1:*
# Select the directory ID of the directory you want to know:
{code:sql}
SELECT * FROM cwd_directory;
{code}
# Run the following query replacing the {{<id_from_directory>}} with the chosen ID from the previous query:
#* Users: {code:sql}
SELECT user_name FROM cwd_user WHERE directory_id = <id_from_directory>;
{code}
#* Groups: {code:sql}
SELECT group_name FROM cwd_group WHERE directory_id = <id_from_directory>;
{code}

*Alternative 2:*
#* List {{user_name | directory_name | directory_id}} ordered by _directory_name_, _user_name_
{code:sql}
SELECT cu.user_name, cd.directory_name, cu.directory_id FROM cwd_user cu INNER JOIN cwd_directory cd ON cu.directory_id = cd.id ORDER BY cd.directory_name,  cu.user_name;
{code}
#* List {{group_name | directory_name | directory_id}} ordered by _directory_name_, _group_name_
{code:sql}
SELECT DISTINCT cg.group_name, cd.directory_name, cg.directory_id FROM cwd_group cg INNER JOIN cwd_directory cd ON cg.directory_id = cd.id ORDER BY cd.directory_name, cg.group_name;
{code}

