In many large enterprises, space creation is locked down. Users have to request spaces through some manual process (specific to each company)

This issue is to track the ability for end-users to request spaces. In requesting a space this will notify site admins that a space has been requested, provide a link to approve or reject it with a message. We should admin screen listing all the pending space requests and past ones and their status. 

The creation of the new space should make the requestor the space admin, notify them that the space has been created with some next steps and also make them the creator of the space (so that the creator of the homepage name is the requestor, not the admin)

